# DESIGN SYSTEM RULES — DO NOT VIOLATE

## Typography
- Body / UI: Geist Sans (loaded via next/font/google → Geist)
- Code / token values: Geist Mono (next/font/google → Geist_Mono)
- NEVER introduce a serif font. NEVER use Source Serif, Times, Georgia, or any serif fallback. If a serif appears in the rendered output, the font import is broken — fix it.
- NEVER use a monospace font for ALL CAPS labels, kickers, eyebrows, footer chrome, status pills, or nav. Mono is for code-equivalent content only.
- Type scale (use these exact sizes):
  - display 64px / 1.05 / -0.025em / 600
  - h1 48px / 1.1 / -0.02em / 600
  - h2 28px / 1.2 / -0.01em / 600
  - h3 20px / 1.3 / -0.005em / 600
  - body-lg 18px / 1.55 / 400
  - body 16px / 1.6 / 400
  - small 14px / 1.5 / 400
  - caption 12px / 1.4 / 0.04em / 500 (NOT mono, use letter-spacing for the kicker feel)
  - code 13px / 1.5 / 400 (Geist Mono — only for token values, code blocks, agent demo content)

